 a challenge to their hereditary power over commoners. The king’s government comprised seigneurial jurisdictions and venal offices. Lordships and offices upheld inequality on behalf of the nobility and bred the discontent motivating the people to make the French Revolution.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFeudalismzFrancexHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh  aAbsolutist state.  aBerry.  aEarly modern France.  aFeudalism.  aLyon.  aPoitou.  aProvincial assemblies.  aRevolution.  aSocial class analysis.  aVenality of Office.1 aMiller, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614838440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526148384423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526148384/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles